  "prompt": "What is the best way to remember my dreams when I wake up?",
  "response": "Here are some effective ways to help remember your dreams:\n\n1. Keep a dream journal\n- Place it and a pen next to your bed\n- Write down your dreams immediately upon waking\n- Even partial memories or fragments are helpful\n\n2. Improve your sleep habits\n- Get consistent, adequate sleep\n- Avoid alcohol and heavy meals before bed\n- Maintain a regular sleep schedule\n\n3. Practice dream recall techniques\n- As you wake up, lie still and try to remember your dreams\n- Focus on any emotions or images you recall\n- Don't move too quickly when first waking up\n\n4. Set an intention before sleeping\n- Tell yourself you want to remember your dreams\n- Visualize remembering your dreams when you wake up\n\n5. Use supplements or techniques\n- Some people find vitamin B6 helps dream recall\n- Try meditation or mindfulness before bed\n- Practice reality checks during the day\n\n6. Wake up more gradually\n- Use a gentle alarm\n- Use an alarm that wakes you during lighter sleep stages\n- Try smart alarm apps that track sleep cycles\n\n7. Get enough quality sleep\n- Ensure you're getting 7-9 hours of uninterrupted sleep\n- Create a comfortable sleep environment\n\nConsistency is key in improving dream recall.",
